Judy Tassell (pgjtasse@atlas.cs.upei.ca) wrote:
:   A query: is there any program that I can give a sequence of encoded
: characters (13 characters, both upper and lower case) and what their
: decrypted value is, and the program would derive the algorithm?  I mean the
: sort of thing where you enter like 50 sequences (more would be possible) and
: it gets the encryption meathod?  I just thought it would be an interesting
: program for testing out the security of various encryption meathods, or
: breaking them.  I'd really appretiate a copy of any program that will do
: this, even if just a demo....
: -Charles Tassell


Sure.  It's a very simple one: "XOR with the one's complement of the
encoded and decrypted values".  :-)

But seriously, there are an infinite number of algorithms that can
do an arbitrary mapping.  You have to constrain the class of algorithms more.


